  "original_title": "Rs. 17.85 Million cash recovered inside President\u2019s House: Police yet to keep recovered money in judicial custody",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rs. 17.85 Million cash recovered inside President\u2019s House: Police yet to keep recovered money in judicial custody",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It was transpired before Colombo Fort Magistrate's Court that even after the lapse of three weeks, the Fort Police is yet to keep Rs. 17.85 Million in cash recovered from the President's House, under judicial custody.",
        "Taking into consideration the facts, Colombo Fort Magistrate Thilina Gamage today issued an order directing the OIC of Fort police to immediately produce in court, a sum of Rs. 17.8 Million recovered by protesters inside President's House on 9th July.",
        "Colombo Fort Magistrate Thilina Gamage made this order when the four suspects arrested for forcibly entering the President's House on the 9th of July were produced before Court by Slave Island Police.",
        "Defence Counsel appeared on behalf of the suspects and alleged that police have arrested four individuals out of thousands of people who entered the President's House following the 9th of July incident. They submitted to the court that individuals who acted to hand over the recovered money to the Fort Police have been arrested unreasonably.",
        "Refusing a request made by Slave Island police to remand the suspect, the Magistrate ordered to release of each suspect on a surety bail of Rs.500,000.",
        "President's Counsel Rienzie Arsekularatne with counsel Sunil Watagala, Chamindri Arsekularatne, Udara Muhandiramge and Nuwan Bopage appeared for the suspects.(Lakmal Sooriyagoda)"
      ],
